[2026-03-09 15:04:25] [1d5c3289-82f5-47bd-941c-b7c9d068124c] TOOL: Bash | INPUT: {"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('sample.html', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Get the full message block structure for one message\n# The message div is: <div class='RLrADb' data-message-id='...'>\n# Let's get the immediate children structure\n\n# Find the first message and trace its structure\nidx = content.find('class=\\\"RLrADb\\\" data-message-id=\\\"spaces/bswISxdKVbwB/messages/1773035015853231\\\"')\n# Get a good chunk after\nchunk = content[idx:idx+1500]\n\n# Show the div nesting structure (simplified)\ndepth = 0\ntags = re.finditer(r'<(/?)div([^>]*)>', chunk)\nfor m in tags:\n    closing = m.group(1)\n    attrs = m.group(2).strip()\n    if closing:\n        depth -= 1\n        if depth <= 0:\n            print('  ' * depth + '</div>')\n            break\n    else:\n        cls = re.search(r'class=\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"', attrs)\n        jsname = re.search(r'jsname=\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"', attrs)\n        cls_str = f' class=\\\"{cls.group(1)}\\\"' if cls else ''\n        jsname_str = f' jsname=\\\"{jsname.group(1)}\\\"' if jsname else ''\n        # Check for text content right after\n        end_pos = m.end()\n        next_text = re.match(r'([^<]+)', chunk[end_pos:])\n        text_str = f' → \\\"{next_text.group(1).strip()}\\\"' if next_text and next_text.group(1).strip() else ''\n        print('  ' * depth + f'<div{cls_str}{jsname_str}>{text_str}')\n        depth += 1\n\"","description":"Show message div structure"}
[2026-03-09 15:42:08] [1d5c3289-82f5-47bd-941c-b7c9d068124c] TOOL: Bash | INPUT: {"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('sample.html', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Check if there's a sender name element - look at the Ss4fHf block which groups messages\n# The parent .Ss4fHf contains a timestamp and messages from the same sender\nidx = content.find('class=\\\"Ss4fHf')\nchunk = content[idx:idx+3000]\n\n# Find sender name - look for common patterns\nprint('=== Looking for sender elements ===')\n# Check for any element before the message that might be a name\nbefore_msg = content[idx:content.find('data-message-id', idx)]\nnames = re.findall(r'>([A-Za-z\\u3040-\\u9fff][^<]{0,30})<', before_msg)\nfor n in names:\n    n = n.strip()\n    if n and len(n) < 50:\n        print(f'  Potential sender text: \\\"{n}\\\"')\n\n# Also check the aria-live parent structure\nprint()\nprint('=== aria-live container ===')\naria_idx = content.find('aria-live=\\\"polite\\\"')\naria_chunk = content[aria_idx:aria_idx+200]\nprint(aria_chunk[:200])\n\n# Check what's the direct parent class of the message container\nprint()\nprint('=== Message grouping ===')\n# .Ss4fHf groups messages by sender, .beTDc contains individual messages\n# Check for sender name inside .Ss4fHf but outside .beTDc\nss4_start = content.find('class=\\\"Ss4fHf')\nbetdc_start = content.find('class=\\\"beTDc\\\"', ss4_start)\nbetween = content[ss4_start:betdc_start]\ntexts = re.findall(r'>([^<]+)<', between)\ntexts = [t.strip() for t in texts if t.strip()]\nprint('Text between Ss4fHf and first beTDc:')\nfor t in texts:\n    print(f'  \\\"{t}\\\"')\n\"","description":"Find sender name structure"}
[2026-03-09 15:42:40] [1d5c3289-82f5-47bd-941c-b7c9d068124c] TOOL: Bash | INPUT: {"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('sample.html', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Verify: for each message, what is the text in jsname=dTKtvb?\npattern = r'data-message-id=\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"[^>]*jscontroller=\\\"RrV5Ic\\\".*?jsname=\\\"dTKtvb\\\"><div>([^<]*)</div>'\nmatches = re.findall(pattern, content)\nprint('Messages found via jsname=dTKtvb:')\nfor mid, text in matches:\n    short_id = mid.split('/')[-1]\n    print(f'  {short_id}: \\\"{text}\\\"')\n\n# Also check: does findChatContainer strategy 1 work?\n# aria-live=polite with children -> yes, class Ge9Kpc z38b6\n# Does strategy 2 work? data-message-id parent -> .beTDc\nprint()\n\n# Check: what does the current extractText do on these elements?\n# Current: skip first child, concat rest\n# The RLrADb message div has one child: .jO4O1\n# .jO4O1 has one child: .ptNLrf\n# So skipping first child = skipping the ONLY child = empty string!\nprint('Problem: RLrADb > .jO4O1 is the ONLY child, so slice(1) returns nothing')\nprint('Fix: extract text from [jsname=dTKtvb] instead')\n\"","description":"Verify message text extraction"}
