[2026-03-09 15:51:41] [1d5c3289-82f5-47bd-941c-b7c9d068124c] CLAUDE: Fixed. The `extractText` now queries `[jsname="dTKtvb"]` inside the message element and extracts text from its children — matching the real Google Meet DOM where:  - `<div class="RLrADb" data-message-id="...">` is the message root - Text lives at `[jsname="dTKtvb"] > div` (not as a sibling after a sender element) - Sender name and timestamps are at the group level, not inside individual messages 
